===Etymology===
From the Middle English forms [[veir]] and [[vairé]], meaning "variegated fur", both originally from the {{F.}} [[vair#French|vair]], itself from the {{L.}} [[varius]], "variegated".

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/veɪr/}} (''US'')

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}

#{{tincture}}: An [[heraldic]] [[fur]] formed by a regular [[tesellation]] of blue and white [[bell]] shapes.

